Which year India joined the United Nations
column10: India joined on October 30th 1945. United nations is an international organization founded in 1945 to maintain peace and develop friendly relations among nations

column4: Which state in India Ajanta Caves are located
column10: The Ajanta Caves are located in Aurangabad district of Maharashtra state of India. It has 30 rock-cut Buddhist cave monuments which includes paintings and sculptures

column4: The first Indian elected for British Parliament (Member of Parliament)
column10: In 1892 Dadabhai Naoroji was elected Liberal MP for Finsbury Central. He was from Khadak located near Mumbai.
